7. No Secret Material

This repository must not include:

private keys
passwords
API tokens
live credentials
production secrets
unredacted personal identifiers
private NOEMA memory packets
non-public CIEL identity anchors

If such material is accidentally committed, it must be treated as compromised and removed from public distribution. Keys and credentials must be rotated.

8. Security and Non-Claims

This project is experimental unless a release explicitly states otherwise.

The protocol does not claim:

guaranteed anonymity
guaranteed encryption unless configured
trusted execution
quantum communication
faster-than-light communication
physics-breaking communication
automatic proof of personhood
automatic proof of legal identity
global consensus
production security without audit

Implementations must not advertise these properties unless they are independently implemented, tested, and documented.

